<taxonomicName authorityName="Adanson" authorityYear="1763" box="[258,362,1993,2014]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="7" pageNumber="297" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[258,362,1993,2014]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="297">Kalanchoe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
× 
<emphasis box="[381,470,1993,2014]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="297">forbesiae</emphasis>
commemorates Helena M.L. Forbes (1900–1959). Photographer unknown. Photograph © of the South African National Biodiversity Institute. Reproduced with permission.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="8.[136,1452,158,473]" box="[189,1361,158,185]" pageId="8" pageNumber="298">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,380,158,184]" pageId="8" pageNumber="298">Flowering time:</emphasis>
—August to September, peaking from late-winter to early-spring, southern hemisphere.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[136,1452,158,473]" pageId="8" pageNumber="298">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,314,194,220]" pageId="8" pageNumber="298">Eponymy:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Adanson" authorityYear="1763" box="[342,463,194,220]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="8" pageNumber="298" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[342,463,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="298">Kalanchoe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
× 
<emphasis box="[492,596,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="298">forbesiae</emphasis>
is named for Helena Madelain Lamond Forbes (Forfar, 
<collectingRegion box="[1278,1351,194,220]" country="United Kingdom" name="Angus" pageId="8" pageNumber="298">Angus</collectingRegion>
County, 
<collectingCountry box="[136,237,230,256]" name="United Kingdom" pageId="8" pageNumber="298">Scotland</collectingCountry>
, 
<date box="[250,471,230,256]" pageId="8" pageNumber="298" value="1900-09-11">11 September 1900</date>
–Durban, 
<collectingRegion box="[586,872,230,256]" country="South Africa" name="KwaZulu-Natal" pageId="8" pageNumber="298">KwaZulu-Natal province</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[885,1032,230,256]" name="South Africa" pageId="8" pageNumber="298">South Africa</collectingCountry>
, 
<date box="[1046,1255,230,257]" pageId="8" pageNumber="298" value="1959-09-05">5 September 1959</date>
) (
<figureCitation box="[1281,1352,230,257]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="7.[136,229,1993,2015]" captionTargetBox="[209,1378,353,1967]" captionTargetId="figure-110@7.[209,1378,353,1967]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 7. Kalanchoe ×forbesiae commemorates Helena M.L. Forbes (1900–1959). Photographer unknown. Photograph © of the South African National Biodiversity Institute. Reproduced with permission." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5800560" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5800560/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="298">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
). Forbes was appointed as a junior assistant at the Natal Herbarium (Herb. NH; now the 
<collectingRegion box="[1037,1213,266,292]" country="South Africa" name="KwaZulu-Natal" pageId="8" pageNumber="298">KwaZulu-Natal</collectingRegion>
Herbarium) in 1919. From 1936 to 1937 she spent time at the Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew, and afterwards at the National Herbarium in Pretoria (Herb. PRE), from 1938 to 1940. In 1940 she returned to the then Natal Herbarium to be its curator until she retired in 1955 (
<bibRefCitation author="Gunn, M. &amp; Codd, L. E." box="[313,593,374,401]" pageId="8" pageNumber="298" refId="ref3240" refString="Gunn, M. &amp; Codd, L. E. [W.]. (1981) Botanical exploration of southern Africa. An illustrated history of early botanical literature on the Cape flora. Biographical accounts of the leading plant collectors and their activities in southern Africa from the days of the East India Company until modern times. A. A. Balkema, Cape Town, 400 pp." type="book" year="1981">Gunn &amp; Codd 1981: 156</bibRefCitation>
). She was an authority on the flora of 
<collectingRegion box="[1011,1187,374,400]" country="South Africa" name="KwaZulu-Natal" pageId="8" pageNumber="298">KwaZulu-Natal</collectingRegion>
and among the taxa she described from the province was 
<taxonomicName authority="Forbes (1941: 37)" authorityName="Forbes" authorityPageNumber="37" authorityYear="1941" box="[505,843,410,436]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="8" pageNumber="298" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="albiflora">
<emphasis box="[505,635,410,436]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="298">K. albiflora</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Forbes, H." box="[641,843,410,436]" pageId="8" pageNumber="298" pagination="37 - 41" refId="ref3168" refString="Forbes, H. (1941) Kalanchoe albiflora H. Forbes, sp. nov., pp. 37 - 39. In: Anonymous, Newly described species and new combinations. Bothalia 4: 37 - 41, + plate on p. 39. [https: // archive. org / details / bothaliavolume 404 unse / page / 36 / mode / 2 up]" type="journal article" year="1941">Forbes (1941: 37)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, a name that is today widely included in the synonymy of 
<taxonomicName authority="Hamet (1908: 256)" authorityName="Hamet" authorityPageNumber="256" authorityYear="1908" box="[166,491,446,473]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="8" pageNumber="298" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="luciae">
<emphasis box="[166,267,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="298">K. luciae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Hamet, R." box="[274,491,446,473]" pageId="8" pageNumber="298" pagination="254 - 257" refId="ref3314" refString="Hamet, R. (1908) Kalanchoe luciae sp. nov. Bulletin de l'Herbier Boissier, ser. 2, 8: 254 - 257. [https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / item / 104945  page / 290 / mode / 1 up]" type="journal article" year="1908">Hamet (1908: 256)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
